This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it discusses the reformulation of computer vision problems over Riemannian manifolds and validates the proposed framework on several computer vision applications. It is also likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it proposes a new framework for clustering analysis, which is a common task in these fields. Additionally, the paper mentions the computational complexity of the proposed framework, indicating that it may belong to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new method for clustering on Riemannian manifolds, which falls under the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
